cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the effect of buffering relays on the end-to-end delay of users' data in a network. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper studies the Bernoulli distributed channel conditions and uses intuitive generalizations to conclude the effect of buffering relays on the end-to-end delay. This involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the use of buffers at relays to improve the performance of the system. This falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the improvement in system throughput and end-to-end delay in the settings of practical systems. This may involve the use of multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly discuss cryptography and security, the use of buffering relays may have implications on the security of the system.
